## 📋 Workflow

1. Plan architecture first
2. Check `variables.css` for available values
3. Use existing classes before creating new ones
4. Add missing CSS to the appropriate file
5. Auto error handling with `console.log` solutions

---

## 🚨 Auto Error Handling

```typescript
// composables/useErrorHandler.ts
const logError = (error: Error, context?: string) => {
  console.group(`🚨 ${error.constructor.name}: ${error.message}`);
  console.info("🔧 Solution:", getSolution(error.message));
  console.log("📝 Context:", context);
  console.groupEnd();
};
```

**Solutions Map:** `Cannot find name` → remove manual import | `Cannot find module` → `npm install` | `ref/useHead` → Nuxt auto-imports, remove import

